               <span class="bodySubtitle">Sr. Staff Software Engineer</span><br/>
               This position is in the SSERL of Mot Labs and focuses on software and systems productivity.
               <br><br>
               Contribute to improving SW quality by participating in process improvement including process modeling, simulation, DMAIC projects, FMEA analysis, and statistical data analysis.
               <br><br>
               Drives execution excellence, process compliance and continuous improvement in all aspects of software development by working alongside and with sector teams and Mot Labs.  Tracks, audits and reports on program conformance with process and phase requirements in accordance with established milestones and metrics.
               <br><br>
               Identifies systemic process issues both through auditing or customer complaint and working with the appropriate Process Champion to implement changes, drive closure and prevent re-occurrence. (Step 7, as outlined in the Ford 8 Discipline Problem Solving Process.)
               <br><br>
               Develops and delivers training to close education and knowledge gaps resulting in process non-compliance.
               <br><br>
               Participates as an assessor in the cross-site internal audit program and supports external third party audits of Software Quality.
               <br><br>
               BS or equivalent in Computer Science, Software/Electrical Engineering, Mathematics or related field. 2+ years experience in Software Quality Assurance. SEI CMM, ISO 9000-3 (prefer ISO 9000:2000) or SPICE Auditor. Excellent interpersonal / communication skills Ability to effectively operate and communicate in a multi-cultural environment. Effective presentation skills.   Candidate should understand the concepts of Six Sigma DMAIC and DMADV, CMM and statistical analysis. Should be proficient with Minitab, and have familiarity with modeling and simulation tools. Must be able to write project plans and present results to diverse audiences. Technical writing is required.
               <br><br>
               Specific Skills Required:
               <ol class="bodyText">
               <li>Good technical analytical skills.</li>
               <li>Ability to work within a team environment.</li>
               <li>Ability to multitask.</li>
               <li>Good organizational/time management skills.</li>
               <li>Ability to work under minimal supervision.</li>
